START_COMMIT_MSG: Reworked code for the calendar cells to use a custom control which is based on the previously used button class. This made a whole bunch of separate button layouts obsolete :-). The calendar cells are now marker with a "nicer" "today" marker (not just a plain circle any longer ;-)) and there are symbols to indicate the start of period and the calculated day of ovulation. Partly painted cells for the transition between fertile and infertile days will now also be possible. In later versions there may also be a third symbol on the opposite edge to indicate stored entries for temperature etc. for this day.
REMOVAL_COMMIT_MSG: Updated target API level to Android 4.4. Updated version number for the next release. Code cleanup and optimization. Modified color scheme - there are now "empty" cells to indicate time ranges before and after the current known cycles and predicted period days now also display days with white text.

START_COMMIT_MSG: The project has changed to use the new NBAndroid plugin... therefore the project layout has changed and now uses the building mechanisms built in to the Android SDK. The application now has a better defined bus times parser which has been abstracted out. It is now possible to have a list view of the nearest bus stops to the device's location. This addresses issue 17... however it will not be closed yet as further work needs to be undertaken. Issue 19 has been closed as users are now able to filter bus services.
END_COMMIT_MSG: After the previous commit... I noticed that BusStopMapActivity had the potential to crash with a NullPointerException... this has been fixed. Also... included the patch in issue 20... however the text has been changed slightly.
REMOVAL_COMMIT_MSG: The bus times fetching and Twitter feed fetching tasks have now been partially rewritten as AsyncTask tasks which should aid in code maintainability. The bus stop map can now accept stop codes in the calling Intent for zooming in to a particular stop. DisplayStopDataActivity now shows how long it has been since the last data refresh... which addresses a feature request and closes issue 16. FavouriteStopsActivity now shows a list of bus services for each saved stop and now lets users zoom to that stop on the map in the context menu. The preferences have been reordered for more logical ordering. Added a user preference where the user can elect to show the list of favourite bus stops on application start up rather than the menu. Modified a few of the custom list adapters to use convertView for faster layout drawing. NearestStopsActivity now uses some helpful hints found at http://android-developers.blogspot.com/2011/06/deep-dive-into-location.html

START_COMMIT_MSG: Added an icon to show locations retrieved from geocoding. Modified the search results layout to reflect this. The search results now sort by how close they are to the device's determined location if a location is available. The search functionality is now considered implemented which means that issue 4 is now closed. Fixed issue 15 meaning that hopefully the data retieval threading problem is now finally laid to rest. Modified a Twitter error string to be a bit more descriptive.
END_COMMIT_MSG: After the previous commit... I noticed that BusStopMapActivity had the potential to crash with a NullPointerException... this has been fixed. Also... included the patch in issue 20... however the text has been changed slightly.
REMOVAL_COMMIT_MSG: The bus times fetching and Twitter feed fetching tasks have now been partially rewritten as AsyncTask tasks which should aid in code maintainability. The bus stop map can now accept stop codes in the calling Intent for zooming in to a particular stop. DisplayStopDataActivity now shows how long it has been since the last data refresh... which addresses a feature request and closes issue 16. FavouriteStopsActivity now shows a list of bus services for each saved stop and now lets users zoom to that stop on the map in the context menu. The preferences have been reordered for more logical ordering. Added a user preference where the user can elect to show the list of favourite bus stops on application start up rather than the menu. Modified a few of the custom list adapters to use convertView for faster layout drawing. NearestStopsActivity now uses some helpful hints found at http://android-developers.blogspot.com/2011/06/deep-dive-into-location.html

START_COMMIT_MSG: Removed old artwork and added new artwork. Put in changes for new user interface as well as going for Honeycomb/ICS support. Added support for new JSON API from CEC. Added support for new database updating method. Continued adding support for proximity and time based alerts.
END_COMMIT_MSG: Added a backup agent so that user preferences can be stored in Google Backup. Added intent filter for DisplayStopDataActivity so that other applications can easily interface with the application to load bus stop times. Fixed an issue in the map search results list on certain devices where the row background colour was the same colour as the text. Made the ActionBar transparent in the bus stop map for devices running Honeycomb or later. Added link to project Twitter feed. Added a user preference where the user can specify how many departures per service is shown at each bus stop. For turning on GPS... the correct settings activity is loaded on Ice Cream Sandwich now which closes issue 26. Added locality support in the bus stop database. Navigating the map should be a bit smoother now. Added bus stop direction markers on the bus stop map which closes issue 22. Added better sanity checking around launching the QR scanning activity to prevent crashes which closes issue 27. Re-wrote the Twitter parser to abstract it away from the UI code.
REMOVAL_COMMIT_MSG: Made changes based on recommendations from the lint tool... and removed unused strings. Preferences has been renamed to Settings. This also no longer appears in the ActionBar on Honeycomb and above... following recommendations at the Android design site. Changed Settings display based on these recommendations also. Made plenty of changes in BusStopDatabase and SettingsDatabase to follow good practices and possible performance enhancements.

START_COMMIT_MSG: Add codec negotiation mechanism based on SDP offer and answer. Also includes G.711 u-law support.
END_COMMIT_MSG: string completion for french translation to fit original strings
REMOVAL_COMMIT_MSG: sipdroid: redo codec infrastructure to support arbitrary codecs Instead of having the GSM codec as special... this patch uses a plugin infrastructure to support the adding of arbitrary codecs to Siproid. It also changes the way users select codecs by adding a new 'Audio Codecs' preference screen and allowing them to select for each codec when it will be used (always... edge only or never) and also allowing them to change the order in which codecs are presented to the other end. This code also fixes a bug in the original implementation where on an incoming call... we could be presented with a codec we support that actually has a different media identifier number in the session descriptor. On incoming... it is the remote who chooses the media identifier numbers to use... so we have to do a string comparison to see if we support it and then globally use the remote's media identifier number. I also added the codec being used to the in call screen and a long delay call disconnect dialog if we find a codec mismatch on either incoming or outgoing. Signed-off-by: James Bottomley <James.Bottomley@HansenPartnership.com>

START_COMMIT_MSG: Lots of improvements including AAC file support... icons on main select screen... toast... and assigning ringtones to contacts.
REMOVAL_COMMIT_MSG: Use newer API to decode/encode audio files; fix bugs and deprecated code. Remove the CheapSoundFile classes and use newer APIs (16) instead to decode and encode audio files using the hardware audio encoder/decoder directly. This allows Ringdroid to decode more files (.ogg files for example)... and get all the samples instead of just one approximate value per frame. However it takes longer to decode big audio files. The new audio files created by the app will be encoded in MP4 (.m4a). The MediaPlayer class is not used anymore to play the audio tracks. It is replaced by a custom player based on AudioTrack. Ringdroid won't use the device recording app anymore (not working on Nexus 5 running Lollipop for example). Instead it will record directly the audio using the AudioRecord class. This commit should fix all the major crashes (if not all)... but has been tested only on a Nexus 5 and a Nexus 7... and on Kit-Kat and Lollipop. It also replaces all deprecated APIs with newer and valid ones. In future commits: app build.gradle gradle gradlew gradlew.bat README.md README.txt settings.gradle Update RingdroidEditActivity so that it uses the samples directly... instead of just one coef per frame (even though Ringdroid has access to all the samples now... it still generates one gain coefficient per "frame" in order not to change the old code too much). app build.gradle gradle gradlew gradlew.bat README.md README.txt settings.gradle Update RingdroidEditActivity to better handle gestures (smooth zoom in/out for example instead of just 5 zoom levels).

START_COMMIT_MSG: Remember switched conversations across screen orientation changes As of now... the activity does not remember whether a conversation is switched across configuration changes (such as screen rotations). Fix this by adding onSaveInstanceState() and onRestoreInstanceState() callbacks in the activity to pass this information to the new instance. To make the implementation of this simpler... all code to configure the MessageListView... which was duplicated in several places in the codebase... has been moved to the MessageListView's constructor. While we're at it... make the padding setting independent of screen density instead of specifying in fixed pixels (equivalent to specifying the value in dp instead of px)... and increase the padding for switched views. This ensures that message text isn't obscured by the gradient at the edges of the ConversationGallery... which started happening when we began caching MessageListViews in the DeckAdapter.

START_COMMIT_MSG: Fix auto-reconnect The current auto-reconnection implementation will only try reconnecting once... immediately after the server is disconnected. This will of course almost always fail if the network is down or otherwise unavailable... so as it stands... enabling auto-reconnect isn't particularly useful. This patch implements multiple retries for auto-reconnect... with the frequency of retries controlled by a preference. The Android alarm infrastructure is used to schedule reconnection attempts; if the phone misses a scheduled attempt while it's asleep... the reconnection will be attempted the next time the phone wakes up.
